prepare

protected void prepare(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache)
                throws matrix.util.MatrixException
Evaluates the from and to type information. Because MX does not handle the to or from side types correctly within XML exports, the from and to side types must be evaluated via a "print relationship ... select fromtype / totype" MQL statement. If this is not done in this way, there is no other possibility to evaluate the information fromTypeAll or toTypeAll.

Overrides:
prepare in class AbstractDMWithTriggers_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
Throws:
matrix.util.MatrixException - if the from / to side types could not be evaluated or the prepare from the derived class failed
See Also:
AbstractDMWithTriggers_mxJPO.triggersStack
To do:
support for from / to relationships

writeObject

protected void writeObject(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                           Appendable _out)
                    throws IOException
Writes all relationship specific information in the TCL update file. The relationship specific information are:
  • hidden flag
  • prevent dupplicates flag (see preventDuplicates)
  • from and to side informations

Specified by:
writeObject in class AbstractAdminObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_out - appendable instance to the TCL update file
Throws:
IOException - if the TCL code to the TCL update file could not be written

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method overwrites the original method to append the MQL statements in the _preMQLCode to reset this relationship. This includes:
  • reset description
  • remove hidden and prevent duplicate flag
  • remove all rules
  • reset from and to information
  • remove all from and to types

Overrides:
update in class AbstractDMWithAttributes_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update
Throws:
Exception - if the update from derived class failed
See Also:
AbstractDMWithAttributes_mxJPO.TCL_PROCEDURE
